  "response": "Here are some tips for approaching people on the metro respectfully:\n\n1. Be aware of social cues and body language\n2. Avoid interrupting if someone seems busy or not interested\n3. Start with a casual, friendly comment about something neutral\n4. Respect personal space and boundaries\n5. Be prepared for the possibility that someone may not want to talk\n6. Keep interactions brief and polite\n7. Consider common interests like reading or something happening nearby\n\nRemember that many people use public transit to relax or decompress, so be considerate and non-intrusive.",
